# FvwmIconMan
#
# FvwmIconMan is a powerful tool to list and manage windows. This
# is used as the window list in the panel or taskbar.
DestroyModuleConfig FvwmIconMan:*
*FvwmIconMan: UseWinList true
*FvwmIconMan: ButtonGeometry 120x20
*FvwmIconMan: ManagerGeometry 1x1
*FvwmIconMan: Background #003c3c
*FvwmIconMan: Foreground #ffffff
*FvwmIconMan: FocusColorset 11
*FvwmIconMan: IconColorset 14
*FvwmIconMan: FocusAndSelectColorset 12
*FvwmIconMan: SelectColorset 12
*FvwmIconMan: IconAndSelectColorset 12
*FvwmIconMan: DrawIcons always
*FvwmIconMan: ReliefThickness 0
*FvwmIconMan: Format "%t"
*FvwmIconMan: Font "xft:Source Sans Pro:Regular:size=12:antialias=true:autohint=true"
*FvwmIconMan: Action Mouse 0 A ret
*FvwmIconMan: Action Mouse 1 A sendcommand IconManClick
*FvwmIconMan: Action Mouse 3 A sendcommand "Menu MenuIconOps"
*FvwmIconMan: Resolution global
*FvwmIconMan: Tips needed
*FvwmIconMan: Sort id

# FvwmForm
#
# FvwmForm is a module that can be used to build a GUI
# form. Used with fvwm-menu-desktop-config.fpl.
# This sets the default colorsets.
*FvwmFormDefault: Colorset 10
*FvwmFormDefault: ItemColorset 13

# Start the Show

Read Colorsets
Read DeskTopPanels
Read Keys
Read Mouse

# other decor
# Read BlueDecor
Read VectorDecor

# Start Function
#
# The start function is run right after fvwm is done reading
# the config file. This function run after each restart
# so using Test (Init) or Test (Restart) can further control
# actions that are run during the first time run (Init) or
# actions that are run after a restart.
DestroyFunc StartFunction
AddToFunc   StartFunction
#+ I Test (Init, f $[FVWM_USERDIR]/.BGdefault) Exec exec fvwm-root $[FVWM_USERDIR]/.BGdefault
#+ I TestRc (NoMatch) Exec exec fvwm-root $[FVWM_DATADIR]/default-config/images/background/bg1.png
# + I Test (Init) Module FvwmBanner

+ I Module FvwmEvent EventNewDesk

# + I Module FvwmButtons DeskTopClock
# + I Module FvwmButtons DeskTopPanel
# + I Module FvwmPager *
# + I Module FvwmPager 0 3
# + I Module FvwmButtons FvwmLaunchBar

# + I Module FvwmButtons FvwmTaskBar
# + I Module FvwmButtons FvwmAppBar
# + I Module FvwmButtons FvwmButtonsMenu

# Set wallpaper
# + I Test (Init) Exec sleep 2; exec fbsetbg -c -r "/mnt/public/images/"

# panels and system tray ========================================

+ I Test (Init) Exec exec "$HOME/bin/fvwm-bar.sh"
+ I Test (Restart) Exec exec "$HOME/bin/fvwm-bar.sh"

+ I Test (Init) Exec sleep 3; exec stalonetray
+ I Test (Restart) Exec exec stalonetray

DestroyFunc ExitFunction
AddToFunc   ExitFunction
+ I Test (!ToRestart) Exec exec rm -f $[HOME]/.fvwm/icon.tmp.*
+ I Test (!ToRestart) Exec exec rm -f $[FVWM_USERDIR]/temp/*icon*
+ I Exec exec killall -q conky
+ I Exec exec killall -q xclock
+ I Exec exec killall -q dclock
+ I Exec exec killall -q stalonetray
+ I Exec exec killall -q polybar
+ I Exec exec killall -q tint2
+ I Exec exec killall -q xfce4-panel
